<h1>About This App</h1>
<p class="lead">The Book Library app lets you browse and search a collection of books and their authors.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Data Sources</h2>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">Data Source 1 — Faker Gem</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>Author data (names, nationalities, and bios) is generated using the <strong>Faker Ruby gem</strong>.</p>
        <p>The Faker gem creates realistic fake data and is commonly used for testing and seeding databases.</p>
        <p><strong>Data structure:</strong> name (string), nationality (string), bio (text)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-md-6">
    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">Data Source 2 — CSV File</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p>Book data is loaded from a <strong>CSV file</strong> stored at <code>db/seeds/books.csv</code>.</p>
        <p>The CSV contains titles, genres, descriptions, and publication years for 50 well-known books.</p>
        <p><strong>Data structure:</strong> title (string), genre (string), description (text), published_year (integer)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Database Schema</h2>
<p>The two datasets are related through a <strong>one-to-many</strong> relationship:</p>
<ul>
  <li>One <strong>Author</strong> can have many <strong>Books</strong></li>
  <li>Each <strong>Book</strong> belongs to one <strong>Author</strong></li>
</ul>



<p>Total records in database: 
  <strong>Authors: <%= Author.count %></strong>, 
  <strong>Books: <%= Book.count %></strong>
</p>